Image Skincare Breakdown for Miles Teller 😍
 
✧ Skincare is an essential step to looking Red Carpet Ready. Thanks to the help of some hero products from Image Skincare, Miles is looking his best for Hollywood's biggest night. With a focus on nourishing ingredients and cutting-edge technology, their products are designed to help you achieve healthy, radiant skin. Here's what I used to get him ready ✨

✧ First up is the @imageskincare 𝐇𝐲𝐝𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐅𝐚𝐜𝐢𝐚𝐥 𝐌𝐢𝐬𝐭, which is perfect for giving your skin a quick refresh whenever you need it. Just a quick spritz and your skin is hydrated and revitalized.

✧ Next, I used @imageskincare 𝐎𝐫𝐦𝐞𝐝𝐢𝐜 𝐁𝐚𝐥𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐀𝐧𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐱𝐢𝐝𝐚𝐧𝐭 𝐒𝐞𝐫𝐮𝐦. It's packed with vitamins C and E, green tea, and hyaluronic acid to give your skin a healthy glow . I love to use this serum with an ice roller or cooling globes to not only help depuff, but also oxygenate your skin.

✧ @imageskincare 𝐁𝐢𝐨𝐦𝐞 𝐒𝐦𝐨𝐨𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐂𝐥𝐨𝐮𝐝 𝐂𝐫𝐞̀𝐦𝐞 is a lightweight moisturizer that's packed with all the good stuff, like jojoba oil, shea butter, and hyaluronic acid. It's the perfect way to keep your skin hydrated and feeling silky-smooth. Use a dime-sized amount and massage into your skin in an upward circular motion after your serum.

✧ For extra moisture on your lips, I'm loving @imageskincare 𝐎𝐫𝐦𝐞𝐝𝐢𝐜 𝐁𝐚𝐥𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐋𝐢𝐩 𝐂𝐨𝐦𝐩𝐥𝐞𝐱. It's packed with avocado oil, shea butter, and a touch of peppermint to ensure your lips aren't dry in this cold weather.

✧ I never want to leave out those hands, so I finished with a little hand massage using @imageskincare 𝐕𝐢𝐭𝐚𝐥 𝐂 𝐇𝐲𝐝𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐇𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐁𝐨𝐝𝐲 𝐋𝐨𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧. It improves skin texture without feeling greasy and its natural, light citrus scent is fresh and energizing.

Here’s how I got #MilesTeller’s handsome red carpet look with some help from @americancrew 😎

✵ To begin, I spritzed 𝐀𝐦𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐜𝐚𝐧 𝐂𝐫𝐞𝐰 𝐏𝐫𝐞𝐩 & 𝐏𝐫𝐢𝐦𝐞 onto Miles’ damp hair evenly from roots to ends and combed through. This product will help to hydrate and nourish the hair while also creating a smooth surface for styling.

✵ Miles has thick, wavy hair so I like to layer a couple of foundation products to achieve the desired look. I started with a quarter-sized amount of 𝐀𝐦𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐜𝐚𝐧 𝐂𝐫𝐞𝐰’𝐬 𝐋𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭 𝐇𝐨𝐥𝐝 𝐓𝐞𝐱𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞 𝐋𝐨𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧. This product is ideal for creating a natural, tousled look that’s perfect for the red carpet.

✵ It will help to add volume and definition to the hair without weighing it down. I layer that with a few sprays of 𝐀𝐦𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐜𝐚𝐧 𝐂𝐫𝐞𝐰 𝐌𝐞𝐝𝐢𝐮𝐦 𝐇𝐨𝐥𝐝 𝐒𝐩𝐫𝐚𝐲 𝐆𝐞𝐥.

✵ Using a diffuser, I dried and finger styled his hair. I made sure not to break up his wave while drying so that the finished result had a more polished look.

✵ Finally, we’re going to add some definition and texture to the hair using 𝐀𝐦𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐜𝐚𝐧 𝐂𝐫𝐞𝐰’𝐬 𝐃𝐞𝐟𝐢𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐏𝐚𝐬𝐭𝐞. This product is perfect for creating a sleek, polished look. It will help to define and shape the hair while also adding texture and volume. I used a nickel sized amount and warmed it up using my fingertips, then worked it through the hair defining pieces as needed.

2023. What a year to remember.

So many firsts happened for me this year. The good. The bad. And the scary.

Got really scary sepsis and stayed in the hospital for a week.

Took one of the best trips
of my life to The Emerald Isle.
Jumped off the 40 ft.
Met some leprechauns and fairies.

Made some new friends. Lost some old friends.

Came back, went under the knife and came out with one less kidney feeling better and better each week.

Endured a ridiculously long writers AND actors strike.

Rescued a really cute puppy. Named him Stanley.

Had the pleasure of working with my amazing clients and meeting many new exciting clients. ♥️ And the rest is to be continued.

Wishing everyone happiness, peace, success and love in the upcoming year. Can’t wait to find out what 2024 has on the docket.

#happynewyear #🎉
